This paper is about the convergence analysis of a gradient-based temporal difference (GTD) algorithm, specifically the two time-scale TD with gradient correction (TDC) algorithm, which is widely used in off-policy learning scenarios. The paper focuses on the non-asymptotic convergence analysis of TDC under a non-i.i.d. Markovian sample path and linear function approximation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
